<item>
            <title>[SOLR-8167] RuleBasedAuthorization plugin bypass with POST requests</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-8167</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We are using the RuleBasedAuthorization plugin. We are using the&lt;br/&gt;
collection-admin-edit permission to secure the collections API.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What I have found is that if I try to, say, create or delete a&lt;br/&gt;
collection using a GET request I am prompted to authenticate as&lt;br/&gt;
expected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If I try the same operation using a POST request, it lets me straight&lt;br/&gt;
through and I can delete collections without authenticating.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I emailed &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=noble.paul&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;noble.paul&quot;&gt;noble.paul&lt;/a&gt; directly about this initially and he has confirmed this as a bug.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
